flowRoot.flowPara: When there aren't any manually created playlists, the sidebar isn't shown.
A play button is shown on hover. This remains while a playlist is being played, and turns into a pause button when hovered.
Sidebar is shown when there are manually created playlists.
Button menu allows a playlist to be removed.
Context menu allows tracks to be added to a different playlist, or to be removed from the current one.
After a playlist is removed, or a track is removed from a playlist, an in-app notification allows the action to be undone.
Renaming a playlist. Editing should be automatically closed if the user switches to a different playlist, or to a different view.
